<p>A long explanation. It takes up way more characters and twice as many lines. Also, no one talks like that. However, Iâ€™ll do something like that before I write. Itâ€™s an outline of what Iâ€™m writing just like I had/shouldâ€™ve done in high school. Here itâ€™s called pseudocode. Not actually code. Not strictly my native problem-solving language. When I pseudocode and read it back, I can learn what I donâ€™t understand about the process. Pseudocode even helps me realize that a shorter way to say it in English could be:</p>

