<p>Here youâ€™ve seen a translation of an idea in English to Javascript. Then we checked our phrase over and thought it was too long and became concise. By changing our code to something readable, weâ€™ve refactored our code. Refactoring is a rewriting of code to improve for readability or performance.</p>

<p>Notice I said OR. Hereâ€™s a story from a family <strong>member</strong> (weâ€™ll call R) that had a job interview at a tech company years ago. They were interviewing for a management role and given a coding problem to solve. The code R wrote looked more like the first for loop above compared to the last one.
â€œI was expecting this in one line.â€ the interviewer said.
